  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, the Department of Commerce has obligated $3.2B on contracts, with 5,968 awards and an average award size of $530K; obligations are down 23.9% year over year and current-year totals are partial. Obligations by fiscal year were $4.5B in FY21, $4.1B in FY22, $5B in FY23, $5.2B in FY24, $4.2B in FY25, and $3.2B in FY26. The largest spending categories in FY2026 to date are Other Computer Related Services ($568M), Computer Systems Design Services ($480M), and Custom Computer Programming Services ($331M), followed by All Other Publishers ($215M) and Ship Building and Repairing ($144M). Top vendors in FY2026 to date include REED TECHNOLOGY AND INFORMATION SERVICES LLC ($213M), ACCENTURE FEDERAL SERVICES LLC ($110M), and LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION ($108M), with additional significant awards to JAG KETCHIKAN, LLC ($99.6M) and BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC ($95.5M). This mix of IT services, publishing, shipbuilding, and professional services accounts for the majority of recorded obligations so far in the fiscal year.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What are the largest spending categories this fiscal year?",
        "body": "The largest categories in FY2026 to date are Other Computer Related Services ($568M), Computer Systems Design Services ($480M), and Custom Computer Programming Services ($331M). Additional notable categories by obligation are All Other Publishers ($215M), Ship Building and Repairing ($144M), and Administrative Management and General Management Consulting Services ($134M). These top categories include both IT services and sector-specific industrial work such as shipbuilding and aircraft manufacturing ($108M)."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the top vendors and what do award patterns look like?",
        "body": "Top vendors in FY2026 to date are REED TECHNOLOGY AND INFORMATION SERVICES LLC ($213M), ACCENTURE FEDERAL SERVICES LLC ($110M), and LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION ($108M). Other major contractors include JAG KETCHIKAN, LLC ($99.6M), BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC ($95.5M), and PERATON INC. ($93.9M). The agency recorded 5,968 awards so far with an average award size of $530K and overall obligations down 23.9% year over year."
      }
    ]
